-- BofA Sued by U.S. for $1 Billion Over Alleged Mortgage Fraud
-- B y   A n d r e w   D u n n
-- 2012-10-24T16:10:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/bofa-sued-by-u-s-for-1-billion-over-alleged-mortgage-fraud.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  was sued by
the U.S. attorney in Manhattan for allegedly engaging in a
scheme to defraud Fannie Mae and  Freddie Mac .  The complaint alleges that Countrywide Financial Corp.,
which was later bought by Bank of America, implemented a loan-
origination process that generated thousands of fraudulent or
defective loans that were sold to Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac,
according to a statement today from the Manhattan U.S.
